:::summary
C++ is a powerful, general-purpose programming language created by Bjarne Stroustrup at Bell Labs in the early 1980s as an extension of C. It adds object-oriented programming, generic programming via templates, and a rich standard library while retaining C's low-level efficiency and control. C++ is widely used for operating systems, game engines, compilers, databases, scientific computing, and any application requiring high performance.
